UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Louis TAYLOR, Defendant-Appellant. No. 148, Docket 23568. United States Court of Appeals Second Circuit. Argued Dec. 15, 1955. Decided Dec. 15, 1955. Vine H. Smith, Brooklyn, N. Y., for appellant. Paul W. Williams, U. S. Atty., for Southern District of New York, New York City (Dennis C. Mahoney, Asst. U. S. Atty., New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before CLARK, Chief Judge, and MEDINA and WATERMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed in open court on the opinion below. D.C., 123 F.Supp. 920.
